  <abstract format="text/plain" language="en" script="Latn">IEEE P1451.2 defines a wired point-to-point interface standard for sensors, specifically30 connectors and communication protocols for SPI, I2C, UART and RS-232-C interfaces together with the corresponding TEDS. This specification focuses on the Communication Modules that connect the TIM and NCAP using the IEEE Std 1451.0-2007 basic standard with brevity as a goal. The purpose of this revision is to make IEEE-1451.2-1997 more usable to a wider set of applications.</abstract>
